# ============================================================
#  Noctis Haven — Environment Variables
#  Copy this file to .env and fill in your values.
#  REQUIRED keys will crash the bot if missing.
#  OPTIONAL keys disable specific features if missing.
# ============================================================


# ── REQUIRED ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Discord bot token.
# Get it at: https://discord.com/developers/applications
# → Your App → Bot → Token → Reset Token
TOKEN=MTUwMDE2MDUwODE5NDcxNzcwNg.G_VmIe.4cMks4XM2BP5fYQhj9_K92DKGLdkk9cYsKjiKs

# Discord application / client ID (the bot's user ID, not the token).
# Get it at: https://discord.com/developers/applications
# → Your App → General Information → Application ID
CLIENT_ID=1500160508194717706

# ── LAST.FM (OPTIONAL) ───────────────────────────────────────
# Required for all /fm commands. Without it, /fm returns an error.
# How to get it:
#   1. Go to https://www.last.fm/api/account/create
#   2. Fill in the form (any app name/description works)
#   3. Copy the API Key — paste it here
LASTFM_API_KEY=a98ca30b9c88102ff180bccddd1b99af


# ── NOTES / LOOPHOLES ─────────────────────────────────────────
#
# 1. TOKEN and CLIENT_ID are the only hard requirements.
#    Missing either will throw at startup.
#
# 2. Spotify requires all three: CLIENT_ID, CLIENT_SECRET, REFRESH_TOKEN.
#    Missing any one of them silently disables Spotify — /play with a
#    Spotify URL will respond with an error message, not a crash.
#
# 3. YouTube cookies are optional but recommended for VPS deployments.
#    Without them, some videos may hit a "bot detected" block.
#    The YOUTUBE_COOKIE value must be a single-line string.
#
# 4. GENIUS_TOKEN and LASTFM_API_KEY are truly optional — the relevant
#    commands check at runtime and reply with a user-facing error if missing.
#
# 5. After editing this file, restart the bot for changes to take effect.
#    With pm2: pm2 restart noctis-haven
#
# 6. Never commit .env to git. The .gitignore already excludes it.
-e 
# Health check endpoint port (for Railway/Render). Set to 0 to disable.
HEALTH_PORT=3000
